LogFile.FinalText: Today many homes have pets, and most people prefer either a dog or a cat. Until now, the soft puppy is more popular than the sweet kitten in the battle for being Denmark's most beloved pet. Whereas a dog's loyality explains its great popularity, numerous cat-lovers favour the independent nature of the cat. While ordinary cat owners find dogs to be independent and filtht, many dog owners see cats as lazy and impersonal. Many pet owners choose a pet that reflext their own personality. When big, strong men buy a big, strong dog, the nature of the dog helps enhance the dog owner's ego. Conversely, feminine women often prefer a beautiful and elegant cat. Normally cats and dogs get along without problems if they are used to eachother. Often times, dog owners and cat owners fight more than dogs and cats.
